 {"id":"br-r37-c1-03","title":"REVIEW: [MEDIUM] edge_connectivity returned float and ignored MultiGraph parallel edges","description":"Two related defects in edge_connectivity: (1) simple Graph path returned a float (e.g. 2.0) via the max-flow pipeline while nx returns an int cardinality (2). (2) MultiGraph path collapsed parallel edges: on K3 with extra parallel edges fnx returned 2.0 vs nx's 3. Fixed by coercing int-valued floats to int before returning, and delegating multigraph inputs to networkx.","status":"closed","priority":3,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-24T00:00:00Z","updated_at":"2026-04-24T00:00:00Z","closed_at":"2026-04-24T00:00:00Z","close_reason":"Fixed: MG/MDG delegate to nx; simple Graph path casts integral float back to int. Verified across K3 simple, DG, MG with/without parallel, MDG — all match nx in value and type.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"br-r37-c1-19x8x","title":"parity: ISMAGS class missing from isomorphism API","description":"NetworkX exposes networkx.algorithms.isomorphism.ISMAGS(graph, subgraph, node_match=None, edge_match=None, cache=None) with is_isomorphic(), isomorphisms_iter(), subgraph_is_isomorphic(), subgraph_isomorphisms_iter(), and largest_common_subgraph(). FrankenNetworkX does not export ISMAGS. Add an ISMAGS wrapper that converts FrankenNetworkX graph objects via _networkx_graph_for_parity and delegates to NetworkX, plus parity tests for constructor signature and core methods.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"cod-networkx","created_at":"2026-04-25T09:25:45.112099160Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-25T09:30:32.434165705Z","closed_at":"2026-04-25T09:30:32.432309961Z","close_reason":"Completed in 2c0f4aa","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"br-r37-c1-5q77h","title":"parity: bipartite matching/cluster/basic/redundancy wrappers missing (12 functions)","description":"networkx.algorithms.bipartite exposes 12 functions not surfaced by franken_networkx: matching family (eppstein_matching, maximum_matching, minimum_weight_full_matching, to_vertex_cover), cluster family (cc_dot, cc_max, cc_min, latapy_clustering, robins_alexander_clustering), basic (degrees, sets), and redundancy (node_redundancy). Add Python wrappers in __init__.py via a new _call_networkx_bipartite_for_parity helper, export at top-level, add to __all__ under bipartite section.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-04-25T20:04:07.582914231Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-25T20:21:47.577934437Z","closed_at":"2026-04-25T20:21:47.575865893Z","close_reason":"Shipped in f6a631a: 12 bipartite wrappers via _call_networkx_bipartite_for_parity helper (cc_dot/cc_max/cc_min routed through nx.algorithms.bipartite.cluster). All verified against nx on K33 + weighted 3x3 bipartite graph.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
+{"id":"br-r37-c1-75r94","title":"parity: coloring strategy_* (8) + matching_dict_to_set (1) wrappers","description":"Two clusters of nx utilities not surfaced. Coloring strategies (used as strategy= argument to greedy_color): strategy_largest_first(G, colors), strategy_random_sequential(G, colors, seed=None), strategy_smallest_last(G, colors), strategy_independent_set(G, colors), strategy_connected_sequential_bfs(G, colors), strategy_connected_sequential_dfs(G, colors), strategy_connected_sequential(G, colors, traversal=bfs), strategy_saturation_largest_first(G, colors). Matching utility: matching_dict_to_set(matching) — converts a {node: partner} dict to a set of (u, v) frozensets. Add Python wrappers in __init__.py exporting at top-level + __all__.","status":"in_progress","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-04-25T23:29:37.916763877Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-25T23:34:39.461199322Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"br-r37-c1-7u6up","title":"parity: community edge_betweenness_partition + greedy_source_expansion missing","description":"Two community-detection helpers from networkx.algorithms.community not exposed by franken_networkx: edge_betweenness_partition(G, number_of_sets, weight=None) and greedy_source_expansion(G, source, ...). Add Python wrappers delegating via _call_networkx_community_for_parity, export at top-level and add to __all__.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-25T12:13:47.981273951Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-25T13:05:50.852667948Z","closed_at":"2026-04-25T13:05:50.850778351Z","close_reason":"Shipped in 4eb0d6d: edge_betweenness_partition + greedy_source_expansion verified on karate","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"br-r37-c1-8vobd","title":"parity: approximation TSP family wrappers missing (christofides, greedy_tsp, simulated_annealing/threshold_accepting_tsp, traveling_salesman_problem, asadpour_atsp, metric_closure)","description":"networkx.algorithms.approximation exposes a TSP/metric family that franken_networkx does not: traveling_salesman_problem, christofides, greedy_tsp, simulated_annealing_tsp, threshold_accepting_tsp, asadpour_atsp, metric_closure. All are pure approximation algorithms with no parity-sensitive Rust counterpart in fnx. Add Python wrappers in __init__.py delegating to nx.algorithms.approximation via a new _call_networkx_approximation_for_parity helper (mirrors community/connectivity helpers). Export at top-level and add to __all__. Verify each on a small graph (cycle_graph(5) for TSP, complete_graph(4) for metric_closure).","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-04-25T17:28:04.863008794Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-25T17:56:54.641577638Z","closed_at":"2026-04-25T17:56:54.638612839Z","close_reason":"Shipped in 07416f9: 7 TSP/metric wrappers via _call_networkx_approximation_for_parity helper. Verified greedy_tsp/christofides/traveling_salesman_problem match nx exactly on K4; asadpour_atsp valid on 3-node digraph; sa/ta_tsp produce valid cycles.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"br-r37-c1-9mdsv","title":"parity: label_propagation_communities return type drift","description":"fnx.label_propagation_communities(G) returns dict_values([{0,1,2},...]) — a dict_values view object — while networkx returns a generator yielding sets. Drop-in code that does isinstance(result, types.GeneratorType) or relies on consuming once will diverge. Convert wrapper to yield sets directly (return iter(...)). File: python/franken_networkx/__init__.py (around line 17175).","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-04-25T05:05:05.214287589Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-25T05:08:52.048798239Z","closed_at":"2026-04-25T05:08:52.046958637Z","close_reason":"Invalid: NetworkX 3.6.1 and legacy oracle both return dict_values; existing wrapper and tests already match.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
-{"id":"br-r37-c1-9yavb","title":"parity: utils.heaps {BinaryHeap, MinHeap, PairingHeap} + classes.function.frozen (4 surfaces)","description":"Two missing utility surfaces: networkx.utils.heaps exposes BinaryHeap, MinHeap, PairingHeap classes used as the default heap= kwarg in stoer_wagner and other algorithms; networkx.classes.function exposes frozen as a no-op exception-raising sentinel attached to frozen graphs by nx.freeze. franken_networkx surfaces neither. Add Python wrappers re-exporting these directly from nx (no graph-conversion needed; they are pure utilities).","status":"in_progress","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-04-25T23:09:42.538123502Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-25T23:14:38.188097112Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
+{"id":"br-r37-c1-9yavb","title":"parity: utils.heaps {BinaryHeap, MinHeap, PairingHeap} + classes.function.frozen (4 surfaces)","description":"Two missing utility surfaces: networkx.utils.heaps exposes BinaryHeap, MinHeap, PairingHeap classes used as the default heap= kwarg in stoer_wagner and other algorithms; networkx.classes.function exposes frozen as a no-op exception-raising sentinel attached to frozen graphs by nx.freeze. franken_networkx surfaces neither. Add Python wrappers re-exporting these directly from nx (no graph-conversion needed; they are pure utilities).","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-04-25T23:09:42.538123502Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-25T23:24:40.588218288Z","closed_at":"2026-04-25T23:24:40.586349930Z","close_reason":"Shipped in 63cc1d9: BinaryHeap/MinHeap/PairingHeap re-exports + frozen sentinel. Verified BinaryHeap insert/min/pop, PairingHeap insert/min, frozen() raises NetworkXError as expected.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"br-r37-c1-bj91d","title":"parity: random_uniform_k_out_graph + reverse_cuthill_mckee_ordering + flow_matrix_row missing (3 utilities)","description":"Three nx utilities not surfaced by franken_networkx: random_uniform_k_out_graph(n, k, self_loops=True, with_replacement=True, seed=None) from generators.directed (k-out random digraph), reverse_cuthill_mckee_ordering(G, heuristic=None) from utils (bandwidth reduction node ordering), and flow_matrix_row(G, weight=None, dtype=float, solver=lu) from algorithms.centrality.flow_matrix (current-flow centrality kernel). Add Python wrappers via _call_networkx_submodule_for_parity, export at top-level, add to __all__.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-04-25T21:11:43.252663714Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-25T21:32:49.845701550Z","closed_at":"2026-04-25T21:32:49.843812193Z","close_reason":"Shipped in e3f2e78: random_uniform_k_out_graph + reverse_cuthill_mckee_ordering + flow_matrix_row wrappers. Verified n=8 k=2 seed=42 nodes/edges match, P8 RCM ordering match, K4 flow_matrix_row count match nx.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"br-r37-c1-cujmq","title":"parity: VF2 GraphMatcher/DiGraphMatcher/MultiGraphMatcher classes missing","description":"networkx.algorithms.isomorphism exposes GraphMatcher, DiGraphMatcher, MultiGraphMatcher, MultiDiGraphMatcher classes for the classical VF2 algorithm with rich API: subgraph_is_isomorphic(), subgraph_isomorphisms_iter(), match(), candidate_pairs_iter(), semantic_feasibility(), syntactic_feasibility(), initialize(). fnx exposes only the top-level functions (is_isomorphic, vf2pp_*) but no Matcher classes. Add wrapper classes that delegate to nx.algorithms.isomorphism via _networkx_graph_for_parity, exporting as fnx.GraphMatcher etc.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"cod-networkx","created_at":"2026-04-25T07:30:43.669346473Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-25T09:18:29.924704555Z","closed_at":"2026-04-25T09:18:29.922845114Z","close_reason":"Completed in 742c813","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"br-r37-c1-d967f","title":"parity: approximation treewidth/steiner/dominating/max-cut/ramsey/densest wrappers missing (10 functions)","description":"After the TSP family (br-8vobd), 10 more approximation algorithms remain unexposed: treewidth_min_degree(G), treewidth_min_fill_in(G), steiner_tree(G, terminal_nodes, weight, method), min_edge_dominating_set(G), min_maximal_matching(G), min_weighted_dominating_set(G, weight), one_exchange(G, initial_cut, seed, weight), randomized_partitioning(G, seed, p, weight), ramsey_R2(G), densest_subgraph(G, iterations, method). All are pure heuristics with no Rust counterpart — add wrappers via the existing _call_networkx_approximation_for_parity helper, export at top-level, add to __all__ under the approximation section.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-04-25T19:34:18.988742298Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-25T19:57:48.971397375Z","closed_at":"2026-04-25T19:57:48.969471288Z","close_reason":"Shipped in 66ec413: 10 approximation wrappers (treewidth_min_degree/min_fill_in, steiner_tree, min_edge_dominating_set, min_maximal_matching, min_weighted_dominating_set, one_exchange, randomized_partitioning, ramsey_R2, densest_subgraph). All verified against nx on K5/C6/P6/K6/C7/BA20 graphs.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
